741
01:10:07,670 --> 01:10:09,013
Revenge.

742
01:10:12,408 --> 01:10:13,944
Vengeance.

743
01:10:14,811 --> 01:10:16,415
Vengeance from whom?

744
01:10:17,013 --> 01:10:17,889
And why?

745
01:10:18,414 --> 01:10:20,724
From a murderer...

746
01:10:20,883 --> 01:10:22,726
for a murder.

747
01:10:27,624 --> 01:10:30,434
You seem to have confused matters.

748
01:10:30,493 --> 01:10:33,633
My father was arrested by the army
and one of these days...

749
01:10:33,696 --> 01:10:36,643
we will find out where
they're holding him.

750
01:10:38,868 --> 01:10:41,940
Let the petals fill with color...

751
01:10:41,971 --> 01:10:44,417
Let the breeze ruffle the spring...

752
01:11:06,696 --> 01:11:09,609
Come along, my love...

753
01:11:09,666 --> 01:11:13,705
Awake the garden to life.

754
01:11:29,819 --> 01:11:34,393
The prison is a sullen ghost...

755
01:11:35,425 --> 01:11:42,570
Ask the breeze for a whiff of hope...

756
01:11:44,768 --> 01:11:50,377
Oh, someone please...

757
01:11:50,440 --> 01:11:56,482
speak of the beauty of my beloved.

758
01:11:56,546 --> 01:12:02,929
- When fatigue would muffle
our screams in the prison...

759
01:12:03,753 --> 01:12:08,133
